From 2ea4f5fc5acd489fe13e40e288be20c1797c5614 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Olivier Benjamin <olivier.benjamin@bootlin.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 09:53:32 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 08/13] imx93_frdm.h: Move heap to fix AHAB boot

By default, SPSDK sets the AHAB container for i.MX93 to load TF-A
in non-secure OCRAM at 0x204E0000 [1].

Unfortunately, when the heap starts at 0x204D0000, early devices
are located there, and end up being overwritten by Tf-A.
Once SPL hands off to the BootROM to jump onto TF-A, the system
crashes with a Secure Exception, due to that corruption.

1: https://github.com/nxp-mcuxpresso/spsdk/blob/master/spsdk/data/devices/mimx9352/database.yaml#L206

Signed-off-by: Olivier Benjamin <olivier.benjamin@bootlin.com>
---
 include/configs/imx93_frdm.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/configs/imx93_frdm.h b/include/configs/imx93_frdm.h
index 987fcacb999..1934670c071 100644
--- a/include/configs/imx93_frdm.h
+++ b/include/configs/imx93_frdm.h
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@
 	(QSPI0_AMBA_BASE + CONFIG_SYS_MMCSD_RAW_MODE_U_BOOT_SECTOR * 512)
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_XPL_BUILD
-#define CFG_MALLOC_F_ADDR		0x204D0000
+#define CFG_MALLOC_F_ADDR		0x204F0000
 #endif
 
 /* Link Definitions */
-- 
